The Commissioner for Insurance, Sunday Thomas, has urged insurance agents to be good ambassadors of the industry as they interface between the industry and society. He spoke during the annual general meeting of ARIAN where new executives were elected to direct the affairs of the agents. “Insurance sector needs more agents to take insurance to the grassroots in the country,” he said. The commissioner, who was represented by the Principal Manager, Licensing & Regulation Intermediaries, NAICOM, Mrs Vera Aimufua, urged the public to only patronise registered and licensed insurance agents. The commission, he said, would continue to support the agents, who he identified as the foot soldiers of the industry. At the event, new executives were elected and Odewunmi Kazeem of Mutual Benefits Assurance Plc emerged as the new president of ARIAN. Jegede Olatunde, of NSIA Insurance Limited, was elected the Vice President; Mrs Constance Lawrence of AIICO Insurance Plc as secretary-general; Oluwatobi Sobande of Consolidate Hallmark Insurance became assistant general secretary; Ogunwuyi Kayode of Old Mutual Insurance became public relations officer. Others are Ajayi Folashade of Leadway Assurance as financial secretary; Catherine Adeyemi of Leadway Assurance Limited as Auditor; Jeremiah Okpako;Olatubosun Mayowa, Mutual Benefits Assurance, Social Secretary and Legal Adviser, Chinonso Eze.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com